text.tspan: The Chinese, who largely settled in urban areas
however, Malays mostly lived in rural areas.
Malaysia also has a peculiar appearance in education.
Primary and secondary schools are divided
into chinese, indian, malay and religous type of schools.
The Chinese population have the lowest poverty rate (0.1%),
the highest average income, and control over 70% of all
commercial real estate in the country,
but why are they still leaving Malaysia?
In terms of the spoken languages, different ethnic
groups skeak various languages in different situations.
From the geographical point of view,
the area where they live is almost separate.
